Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Finely chop the @chives{5%grams} (use #scissors{} if you prefer).

Quarter the @lemon{1%unit}.

Pop the @cream cheese{48%grams} into a #bowl{}.

Add the chives and squeeze of lemon juice. Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

> TIP: To avoid turning on your oven, toast the bagels in the toaster instead.

Halve the @bagels{2%unit} (1 per person, you can save the rest for use later).

Toast in your #toaster{}. Alternatively, toast in the oven for ~{4-6%minutes}.

Once toasted, pop the bagel onto your #plates{} and spread with the chive cream cheese.

Pull the @smoked salmon{100%grams} apart into large pieces and layer on top of the cream cheese.

Eat your bagels either open faced or sandwiched closed—it's up to you!

Serve any remaining lemon wedges alongside.